         <div type="commentary">
            <head>Commentary</head>
            <p>This, the original dedication on the stone, indicates an ephebic monument; for Hermes and Herakles as gods
               of the gymnasium see H. Siska, <title><ref target="https://zenon.dainst.org/Record/000778900">De Mercurio ceterisque deis ad artem gymnicam
                    pertinentibus</ref></title> (1933) esp. p. 3 f. and 38f.</p>
